# ClipForge - Desktop Video Editor
**72-Hour Build Challenge**

## Project Mission
Build a production-grade desktop video editor in 3 days (Oct 27-29, 2024) that handles screen recording, webcam capture, clip import, timeline editing, and video export.

## Deadlines
- **MVP**: Tuesday, October 28th at 10:59 PM CT
- **Final Submission**: Wednesday, October 29th at 10:59 PM CT

## MVP Requirements (Hard Gate - Tuesday 10:59 PM CT)
Must have ALL of these:
- ✅ Desktop app that launches (Electron or Tauri)
- ✅ Basic video import (drag & drop or file picker for MP4/MOV)
- ✅ Simple timeline view showing imported clips
- ✅ Video preview player that plays imported clips
- ⏳ Basic trim functionality (set in/out points on a single clip)
- ⏳ Export to MP4 (even if just one clip)
- ⏳ Built and packaged as a native app (not just running in dev mode)

## Tech Stack (Current)
- **Desktop Framework**: Tauri (in progress) - Rust-based, smaller, faster than Electron
- **Frontend**: Next.js 16.0.0 with React 19.2.0
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4.1.9
- **UI Components**: Radix UI, Lucide React
- **Media Processing**: FFmpeg (for export), HTML5 Video API (for preview)

## Project Structure

### Core Components
- **`components/video-editor.tsx`** (486 lines) - Main controller
  - Video import via drag & drop and file picker ✅
  - Clip management and timeline state ✅
  - Playback controls ✅
  - Keyboard shortcuts (Space, I, O, arrow keys) ✅

- **`components/video-preview.tsx`** (154 lines) - Video display
  - HTML5 video playback with synchronized clip switching ✅
  - Fullscreen support ✅
  - Volume and playback speed controls ✅
  - **Layout**: Uses `h-full w-full object-contain` with proper flex hierarchy

- **`components/timeline.tsx`** - Timeline visualization
  - Visual timeline with zoom controls ✅
  - Clip dragging and arrangement ✅
  - Trim handles for in/out points ✅
  - Split functionality ✅

- **`components/toolbar.tsx`** - Editing tools
  - Split, copy, delete operations ✅

- **`components/export-dialog.tsx`** - Export configuration
  - Resolution presets (4K, 1080p, 720p, 480p) ✅
  - FFmpeg-based video export ⏳

### Data Model
\`\`\`typescript
interface VideoClip {
  id: string          // Unique identifier
  name: string        // Original filename
  url: string         // Blob URL from URL.createObjectURL()
  duration: number    // Full duration in seconds
  startTime: number   // Timeline position
  trimStart: number   // In point (seconds)
  trimEnd: number     // Out point (seconds)
  track: number       // Track number (multi-track support)
}
\`\`\`

